[The Canary Islands is a Spanish archipelago located just off the northwest coast of mainland Africa, 100 km [60 mi] west of the border between Morocco and the Western Sahara. The Canary Islands are a Spanish autonomous community and an outermost region of the European Union. The islands include (from largest to smallest): Tenerife, Fuerteventura, Gran Canaria, Lanzarote, La Palma, La Gomera, El Hierro, La Graciosa, Alegranza, Isla de Lobos, Montana Clara, Roque del Este, and Roque del Oeste. The Canary Islands are legally recognized as a nationality of Spain. Geographically it is a part of the African Continent. The HealthMap interactive map of the Canary islands can be accessed at http://healthmap.org/r/1AYl.

The predominance of the A/(H3N2) influenza virus reflects the pattern observed in mainland Spain, and Western Europe in general at the present time. The current seasonal influenza vaccine should provide adequate protection for the local inhabitants and visitors from mainland Europe. - Mod.CP]
